==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lasher
<hw>Lash"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who whips or
lashes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lasher</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lasher
<hw>Lash"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A piece of rope for
binding or making fast one thing to another; -- called also
<altname>lashing</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A weir in a river.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lashing</ent>⟦br⟧
